Topics cover in ten themes related to culture. Each lesson develops the language skills of reading, speaking, listening, writing. Teaching takes place in thematic blocks, including vocabulary, theoretical grammar, exercises and conversation topics. The material is built on a simple complicated principle. In choosing the methods, the individual and cultural characteristics of the learner are taken into account, the theory is associated with practice, active and pertinent learning is applied. During the course five independent work must be done and an individual dictionary should be prepared. Whenever possible, we go to studying places in cultural history.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course is for foreign students, who will start their studies in Estonian language and spend the first year learning only Estonian. The course supports the development the level of Estonian language to the first language proficiency level (0-> A2). The aims of the course: - introduce students to the Estonian cultural space; - develop all aspects of language learning through the teaching of cultural topics; - apply theoretical knowledge through conversations, audio-visual tools and active learning methods.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who passed the subject: - knows the specifics of the Estonian cultural space in the classroom, can talk about it; - is able to read the relevant texts, speak and write on simpler cultural topics, and can listen to reports on simpler cultural texts; - has written an individual Estonian dictionary for the subject matter; - has applied his theoretical knowledge by visiting cultural places and meeting with cultural figures.
